<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The macro uses a hard-coded UINT32_MAX/2 upper bound. On targets where the type of 'val' (e.g. size_t) cannot reach that value (for example a 16-bit size_t where SIZE_MAX < UINT32_MAX/2), the expression ((val)>0 && (val)<(UINT32_MAX/2)) is always true. That makes the ARGCHECK failure branch (the error-handling path) unreachable, which violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.1. (Use of SIZE_MAX or a compile-time-sized bound would avoid this.)
</scenario>
